goals.question: What is the relationship between fertility and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of fertility vs life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is any correlation between fertility and life expectancy. It can help to identify if countries with higher fertility rates have lower life expectancy and vice versa.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the range of fertility rates across countries. It can help to identify if there are any outliers or if the distribution is skewed.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the range of life expectancy rates across countries. It can help to identify if there are any outliers or if the distribution is skewed.

goals.question: What is the trend of fertility and life expectancy over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of fertility and life_expect over year
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is any trend in fertility and life expectancy over the years. It can help to identify if there is any improvement or decline in these rates over time.

goals.question: What is the distribution of countries based on their fertility and life expectancy classification?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of country_classification based on p_fertility and p_life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the distribution of countries based on their fertility and life expectancy classification. It can help to identify if there are any patterns or trends in the classification of countries based on these rates.

code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='fertility', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='fertility', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median Fertility: {:.2f}'.format(data['fertility'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility across countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='fertility', data=data, label='Fertility')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data, label='Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the trend of fertility and life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Rate')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['p_fertility', 'p_life_expect'])
    data = data.sort_values(by=['country_classification'], ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="country", y="p_fertility", hue="country_classification", data=data, dodge=False)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of countries based on their fertility and life expectancy classification?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
